publicationXrefbbf.standardName: Developmental regulation of monoterpene biosynthesis in the glandular trichomes of peppermint.

pathway.author: [VAishwarya, Marvin M2, DeSl, Fehrhart, Eweitz]

comments.content:
Monoterpenes (C10) are the major group of compounds within the essential oils of the mint (Lamiaceae) family. Peppermint (Mentha  piperita)is considered a model system for the study of monoterpene metabolism, which main steps are depicted in this pathway.


This pathway is annotated well enough for data analysis, however please do not add the "Approved Version" tag yet, since this allocates the PW to the incorrect species (grape vs mint). The WikiPathways team is working on a solution.
